8 A Concurrent Resolution relating to legislative
procedures; and establishing a legislative procedure
9 schedule for the 61st Oklahoma Legislature.
10
11
12 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
13 OF THE 2ND SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE, THE SENATE
14 CONCURRING THEREIN:
15 THAT the First Regular Session of the 61st Oklahoma Legislature
16 shall adhere to the following procedure schedule:
17 1. The First Regular Session of the 61st Oklahoma Legislature
18 shall convene at 12:00 noon on January 5, 2027, for the purposes
19 only of performing the duties set forth in Section 5 of Article VI
20 of the Oklahoma Constitution and organizing pursuant to the
21 provisions of Article V of the Oklahoma Constitution and shall
22 recess no later than 5:00 p.m. on that same day until February 1,
23 2027, beginning at 12:00 noon.
24
ENGR. H. C. R. NO. 1030 Page 1

1 2. December 4, 2026, shall be the final date for requesting the
2 drafting of bills and joint resolutions in the House of
3 Representatives and the Senate for introduction for consideration
4 during the First Regular Session.
5 3. January 14, 2027, no later than 4:00 p.m., shall be the
6 deadline for introduction of bills and joint resolutions in the
7 House of Representatives and the Senate for consideration on the
8 floor of the House of Representatives and the Senate during the
9 First Regular Session. Bills and joint resolutions subsequently
10 introduced, if reported from Committee, shall not be placed on the
11 Calendar for consideration in said house until the first legislative
12 day of the First Regular Session.
13 4. March 25, 2027, shall be the final legislative day for third
14 reading and final passage of a bill or joint resolution in the house
15 of origin.
16 5. May 6, 2027, shall be the final legislative day for third
17 reading and final passage of a bill or joint resolution in the house
18 opposite the house of origin.
19 6. The First Regular Session shall adjourn sine die not later
20 than 5:00 p.m. on May 28, 2027.
21 7. Upon a two-thirds (2/3) vote of the membership of or
22 pursuant to joint rules adopted by both chambers, a bill or joint
23 resolution can be exempt from all deadline dates in both chambers.
24 Upon a two-thirds (2/3) vote of the membership of or pursuant to
ENGR. H. C. R. NO. 1030 Page 2

1 rule s adopted by a single chamber, a bill or joint resolution can be
2 exempt from all deadline dates in that chamber only.
3 THAT the Second Regular Session of the 61st Oklahoma Legislature
4 shall adhere to the following procedure schedule:
5 1. December 3, 2027, shall be the final date for requesting the
6 drafting of bills and joint resolutions in the House of
7 Representatives and the Senate for introduction for consideration
8 during the Second Regular Session.
9 2. January 20, 2028, no later than 4:00 p.m., shall be the
10 deadline for introduction of bills and joint resolutions in the
11 House of Representatives and the Senate for consideration on the
12 floor of the House of Representatives and the Senate during the
13 Second Regular Session.
14 3. The Second Regular Session of the 61st Oklahoma Legislature
15 shall convene at 12:00 noon on February 7, 2028.
16 4. March 23, 2028, shall be the final legislative day for third
17 reading and final passage of a bill or joint resolution in the house
18 of origin.
19 5. May 4, 2028, shall be the final legislative day for third
20 reading and final passage of a bill or joint resolution in the house
21 opposite the house of origin.
22 6. The Second Regular Session shall adjourn sine die not later
23 than 5:00 p.m. on May 26, 2028.
24
ENGR. H. C. R. NO. 1030 Page 3

1 7. Upon a two-thirds (2/3) vote of the membership of or
2 pursuant to joint rules adopted by both chambers, a bill or joint
3 resolution can be exempt from all deadline dates in both chambers.
4 Upon a two-thirds (2/3) vote of the membership of or pursuant to
5 rules adopted by a single chamber, a bill or joint resolution can be
6 exempt from all deadline dates in that chamber only.
7 THAT this schedule shall be inapplicable to any joint resolution
8 introduced for the purpose of disapproving or approving agency rules
9 pursuant to the provisions of the Administrative Procedures Act.
10 THAT this schedule shall be inapplicable to any bills introduced
11 for the purposes of incorporation and merging different versions of
12 a statute amended in more than one measure at the same or different
13 sessions of the Legislature as set forth in Section 23.1 of Title 75
14 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
15 THAT this schedule shall be inapplicable to any bill or joint
16 resolution introduced for the purposes of approving, disapproving,
17 repealing, or modifying rules of the Ethics Commission pursuant to
18 the provisions of Section 3 of Article XXIX of the Oklahoma
19 Constitution.
20 THAT this schedule shall be inapplicable to any bill or joint
21 resolution which proposes a special or local law and for which
22 notice of intended introduction is published in a newspaper for four
23 (4) consecutive weeks pursuant to the provisions of Section 32 of
24 Article V of the Oklahoma Constitution.
ENGR. H. C. R. NO. 1030 Page 4

1 THAT the dates specified in this resolution for introduction of
2 bills or joint resolutions shall be inapplicable to any bill or
3 joint resolution which contains an "RB" number pursuant to the
4 provisions of the Oklahoma Pension Legislation Actuarial Analysis
5 Act. Such measures shall be submitted to the legislative actuary
6 not later than such dates and may be introduced not later than the
7 first Monday in February following such submission.
8 THAT this schedule shall be inapplicable to any bill or joint
9 resolution authored by the chairs and vice-chairs of the House
10 Appropriations and Budget Committee and the Senate Appropriations
11 Committee which affects the receipt, expenditure, or budgeting of
12 state funds or funds under the control of an entity created by state
13 law.
14 THAT this schedule shall be inapplicable to any bill or joint
15 resolution authored by the Speaker of the House of Representatives
16 or the President Pro Tempore of the Senate which is deemed by them
17 to be necessary for the preservation of public peace, health, or
18 safety.
